					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A festival prayer book with services for the special Sabbaths, Pesaḥ and Shavu῾ot according to the German rite.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="135v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מחזור </title>
							<note>
								<p>There is a number of directions in later cursive writing.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="initial">
								<locus n="2r, 8v"/>2 decorated and inhabited initial-word panels, in colours.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">1 decorated initial word in ink.<locus n="22r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">
								<locus n="40r"/>Pen and ink drawing of a hybrid and fleur-de-lis (with the owner's inscription).</decoNote>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="32v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">The four special Sabbaths and Purim</title>
							<note>
								<p>Sheḳalim, folio 1v; Parashah Zekhor, folio 8v; Purim, folio 16r; Parashah Parah, folio 22r; Parashat ha-ḥodesh, folio 26v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="32v" to="38r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Yotser le-Shabat ha-gadol</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="38r" to="88v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Pesaḥ</title>
							<note>
								<p>Ma῾ariv for the first night, folio 38r; shaḥarit, folio 39v; musaf, folio 44v; ma῾ariv for the second day, folio 53r; shaḥarit for the second day, folio 56r; yotser le-Shabat be-ḥulo shel mo῾ed, folio 63v; end of ma῾ariv for the seventh night, folio 71r; shaḥarit for the seventh day, folio 71r; ma῾ariv for the last day, folio 80v, shaḥarit for the last day, folio 81r.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf Add MS 10456.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="88v" to="135v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Shavu῾ot</title>
							<note>
								<p>Ma῾ariv for Shavu῾ot, folio 88v; shaḥarit for the first day, folio 89r; musaf, folio 99v; ma῾ariv for the second day (of R. Shim῾on), folio 113v; ma῾ariv for the third day of Shavu῾ot, folio 117v; the second day of Shavu῾ot, folio 119r.</p>
								<p>The piyuṭim are the same as in Add MS 10456, only some pieces are missing in the series on the Ten Commandments.</p>
								<p>The book of Ruth begins on folio 132r, and the pieces for musaf conclude the volume.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>135 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>385</height>
										<width>300</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>290</height>
										<width>205</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>135 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires, mostly cut away.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves missing after folios 55, 70, 80, 88, 127.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="27" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are hardly distinguishable.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script, punctuated, of the 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Anshel Humel Segal</name> of Frankfurt [am Main]: inscribed, folio 2r, 135v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shim῾on ben Eli῾ezer</name>: inscribed in a pen and ink floral design, Nisan [5]377 (1617): folio 40r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Pre-1600, contemporary. Beige leather, blind tooled, with metal centrepiece, cornerpieces and clasps. Boxed.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Machazor. Ux[...]tum Germanicum. Hebraice.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
